## Likelihood Analysis

\ 2. What outcomes are suggested?

<div class="booktable center-headers">

**Approve**                               **Deny**
-------------                             ----------
[likely] 'Mistake' is discovered.          [likely] No mistake possible.
[unknown] Refugee is saved.                [unknown] Refugee will be killed.
[unknown] Criminal gains entry.            [unknown] Criminal is thwarted.
[unlikely] Earn a credit.                  [likely] Earn a credit.

</div>

::: notes
This step focuses on estimating the likelihood of outcomes from the player's perspective. Here we model a player who is uncertain whether the refugee is actually a criminal and just making up their story.
:::

## Option Analysis {data-transition="slide-in fade-out"}

\ 3. What impacts do the outcomes have on player goals?

<div style="width: 70%; height: 0pt; margin: 12pt auto; border-bottom: 1.5pt solid black;"></div>

<div class="nowrap">
- Four broad categories:
    * <span class="enables">Enables</span> and <span class="threatens">threatens</span> for uncertain effects.
    * <span class="advances">Advances</span> and <span class="hinders">hinders</span> for likely effects.
